      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>F. Clifton White did graduate work at Cornell University from 1945-1947 and was later
            active in Republican political campaigns. He was also a faculty advisor at Ithaca
            College and Cornell University, a social science instructor at Cornell, and a political
            science lecturer at Ithaca College. He is president of F. Clifton White &amp;
            Associates, Inc., a public affairs, political counseling, and government relations
            firm.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Personal papers of F. Clifton White relating to political campaigns from 1960-1970,
            mainly Barry Goldwater's 1964 presidential campaign.</p>
      </scopecontent>
